cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a CNN model for optical flow. The use of pyramidal processing and warping also suggests that it may be related to image processing and computer graphics (cs.MM). The fact that the model is learnable and uses a cost volume suggests that it may also be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the model to estimate optical flow in real-world scenarios suggests that it may be related to robotics (cs.RO).
